author: gstein
msg: More SWIG work. I've added a demo/test program that *works*
* bindings/swig/python/: new directory for the Python-specific SWIG
binding stuff.
* swig/python/setup.py: moved from swig/setup.py. added a copyright
header. added the build of the 'svn' package.
* swig/python/svn/: new directory for the 'svn' package.
* swig/python/svn/__init__.py: new file. bare file to turn this
directory into a package.
* swig/python/svn/fs.py: new file. the "public" portion of the FS
interface.
* swig/pyton/fstest.py: new file. nifty little demo/test program to
dump out a tree of the HEAD revision.

author: gstein
msg: Some work on fixing issue 600.
(unfortunately, this doesn't entirely fix the problem; see the issue)
* adm_crawler.c (report_single_mod): after we called add_directory to
get a new directory baton, we didn't use it. instead, we were
using an entirely bogus baton (tb->editor_baton which is actually
a file_baton, which isn't valid for a diretory in any case).
